&lt;Blue Arrow Plc> said it had agreedterms to acquire a group of U.S. Companies collectively knownas the &lt;Richards Companies>, which specialise in executiverecruitment and management consultancy on personnel matters.    The total consideration will be 29 mln U.S. Dlrs of which50 pct will be payable in cash and 50 pct by the issue of 1.36mln new ordinary shares in Blue Arrow.    The Richard Companies made a pre-tax profit of 3.6 mln dlrsin the year to end-1986, on turnover of 7.1 mln dlrs with nettangible assets at the end of 1986 of 3.4 mln dlrs.    Blue Arrow shares were trading 9p lower at 670 thismorning. REUTER&#3;